# Savitara Platform - Asset Requirements

## Mobile App Assets

### App Icons
Required sizes for iOS and Android:

**iOS:**
- icon.png (1024x1024) - App Store icon
- adaptive-icon.png (1024x1024) - For Android

**Android:**
- Various sizes generated by Expo (handled automatically)

### Splash Screen
- splash.png (1242x2436) - Launch screen background

### Favicon
- favicon.png (48x48) - Web favicon

## Asset Creation Guide

### 1. Create Logo
Recommended specifications:
- Primary Color: #FF6B35 (Orange)
- Secondary Color: #004E89 (Blue)
- Style: Modern, spiritual, trustworthy
- Elements: May include Om symbol, lotus, or traditional Hindu motifs

### 2. Generate Assets with Expo

```bash
cd mobile-app

# Install asset generation tool
npm install -g sharp-cli

# Generate all required sizes
npx expo-optimize
```

### 3. Update app.json
After creating assets, ensure paths in app.json are correct:
```json
{
  "icon": "./assets/icon.png",
  "splash": {
    "image": "./assets/splash.png"
  },
  "android": {
    "adaptiveIcon": {
      "foregroundImage": "./assets/adaptive-icon.png"
    }
  }
}
```

## Temporary Placeholders

For development, you can use placeholder images:

1. Create assets directory:
```bash
mkdir -p mobile-app/assets
```

2. Download free placeholder images from:
- https://placeholder.com/
- https://unsplash.com/ (spiritual/Hindu themed)
- https://www.flaticon.com/ (icons)

## Final Production Assets

Before production deployment, create professional assets:
1. Hire a designer on Fiverr/99designs
2. Use Canva Pro templates
3. Commission from a branding agency

## Asset Checklist

- [ ] App icon (1024x1024)
- [ ] Adaptive icon (Android)
- [ ] Splash screen
- [ ] Favicon
- [ ] Feature graphic (for Play Store)
- [ ] Screenshots (for both stores)
- [ ] Promotional banner
